{"lemma":"كَلِيبَةٍ","slug":"كَلِيبَةٍ","root":"ك.ل.ب","root_slug":"ك-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37150"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rabid, infected with rabies"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clip, short video"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"music video"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From كَلَب (kalab, “rabies”).\n\nFrom فيديو كليب (“fīdiyō klīb”), from English video clip."},"ipa":["/klib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37150","headword_ar":"كَلِيبٌ","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Respecting this word in the following verse of TaäbbataSharran,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA AlHarobu A^awolatoka Alkaliyba fawal~ihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        kaliybaka waA@Eolamo A^an~ahaA sawofa tanojaliY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When war sets over thee &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"] there are two opinions: one, that by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klyb","text_ar":"كليب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukaAlib","text_ar":"مُكَالِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 2): the other, that it is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibati AlHarobu","text_ar":"كَلِبَتِ الحَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ The war became vehement, severe, or fierce ”]: the former is the more valid. (IM.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}